CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 9, 1964, pg. 1 reads:" World-Wide Delegation - The nearly 900 delegates attending the Methodist General Conference in Pittsburgh is world-wide, representing many races that inhabit the globe. The Courier cameraman captured some of these in above pictures. Left Photo: The Rev. Allen M. Mayes, staff member, General Board of Pensions, Evanston, Ill.; Hugh Herbert, Missoula, Mont., and W.T. Handy Sr., pastor, St. Mark's Methodist Church, Baton Rouge, La....-Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Reverend Allen M. Mayes,  Hugh Herbert, and Reverend W.T. Handy Sr., standing in interior during 1964 United Methodist Church General Conference
